2.10	Quail-dove	Quail-dove	Geotrygon is a bird genus in the pigeon and dove family . Its members are called quail-doves and all live in the Neotropics. The 17 species of this genus have ranges from southern Mexico and Central America to the West Indies and South America. Quail-doves are ground-dwelling birds that live, nest, and feed in dense forests. They are remarkable for their purple to brown coloration with light-and-dark facial markings.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/46/Crested_Quail-dove_2506945512.jpg/220px-Crested_Quail-dove_2506945512.jpg
